message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MED, cs.AI, cs.NEURON - The paper deals with automated tumour segmentation in medical images using machine learning techniques, specifically dynamic contrast-enhanced MRI. This falls under the intersection of computer vision (cs.CV) and medical imaging (cs.MED). The use of supervoxels and graphical models also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of deep learning techniques, which could also place it under the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NEURON).
